---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Prayer" description="Nathan Bost — Scripture meditation, prayer practices, and the faith that grounds everything else.">
  <div class="bg-brand-navy min-h-screen">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16">

      <!-- Hero -->
      <header class="mb-16">
        <p class="text-brand-gold text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-3">Prayer & Faith</p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-brand-cream mb-6 leading-tight">
          Faith Is the<br class="hidden sm:block" /> Bedrock.
        </h1>
        <p class="text-brand-cream/70 text-lg max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
          Everything else — work, family, ambition — sits on top of this. I'm a follower of Christ,
          and that shapes how I think about money, technology, community, and purpose.
          This is where I share what I'm learning in Scripture and how I'm learning to pray.
        </p>
      </header>

      <!-- Scripture Meditations -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-brand-gold mb-8">Scripture Meditations</h2>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6">

          <div class="bg-brand-slate/50 border border-brand-slate rounded-xl p-6">
            <div class="text-brand-gold text-2xl mb-3">📖</div>
            <h3 class="text-brand-cream font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Slow Reading</h3>
            <p class="text-brand-cream/60 text-sm leading-relaxed">
              I read Scripture slowly — often the same passage for several days.
              The goal isn't to cover ground but to let the text do its work.
              Lectio divina-influenced, but informal.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-brand-slate/50 border border-brand-slate rounded-xl p-6">
            <div class="text-brand-gold text-2xl mb-3">✍</div>
            <h3 class="text-brand-cream font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Written Reflection</h3>
            <p class="text-brand-cream/60 text-sm leading-relaxed">
              I journal through passages — what's striking me, what I'm resisting,
              what I sense God saying. Writing slows me down enough to actually notice things.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-brand-slate/50 border border-brand-slate rounded-xl p-6">
            <div class="text-brand-gold text-2xl mb-3">🙏</div>
            <h3 class="text-brand-cream font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Praying the Text</h3>
            <p class="text-brand-cream/60 text-sm leading-relaxed">
              Moving from reading to prayer — taking the language of Scripture and turning it
              back toward God. This practice has changed how I pray more than anything else.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-brand-slate/50 border border-brand-slate rounded-xl p-6">
            <div class="text-brand-gold text-2xl mb-3">🌱</div>
            <h3 class="text-brand-cream font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Faithful Consistency</h3>
            <p class="text-brand-cream/60 text-sm leading-relaxed">
              The rhythms matter more than the breakthroughs. Showing up on ordinary mornings
              when nothing feels profound is what forms a person over time.
            </p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- What I believe callout -->
      <section class="bg-brand-slate/30 border border-brand-gold/20 rounded-xl p-8 mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-brand-gold mb-3">What I Believe</h2>
        <p class="text-brand-cream/70 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          I'm a Christian — not in a cultural, nominal sense, but as someone who actually believes
          the resurrection happened and that it changes everything. I attend a local church, try to
          read my Bible most mornings, and believe that faith and reason are friends, not enemies.
        </p>
        <p class="text-brand-cream/50 text-sm">
          This shapes how I approach work, relationships, and the future — and it's why I care
          deeply about things like the ethics of AI and the role of community in a fragmented world.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Content coming -->
      <section class="bg-brand-slate/20 border border-brand-slate rounded-xl p-8 text-center">
        <p class="text-brand-gold text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-3">Coming Soon</p>
        <p class="text-brand-cream/60 leading-relaxed">
          I'm working on publishing some of my Scripture meditations and prayer reflections here.
          Check back, or reach out if you'd like to talk about any of this.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
